Author: dpawson
Content:
Great essay Paul. Some echoes of your Lisp book and Code Complete!

The only downside to working on your own is that you don't see the bugs that you create through not seeing the problem? Others seem to see what you don't? That solo work needs tempering with some level of review.

I chuckled over the effort spent on 'homers', work done (perhaps even for the company) in a persons own time. Boy does that work get some deep concentration and produce some good results!

Thanks Paul. DaveP

Author: ivankirigin
Content:
Government hacking seems extremely rare, probably because of the threat of violence common to countries that need it.

Lots of people fail with the categorical error that the problems with poor countries have something to do with what rich countries do to them. Farm subsidies and other wide reaching regulation aside, they are not poor because we are rich.

My main hope for the developing world is in distributed innovation efforts. I love the idea of someone using a bicycle to charge a cellphone, then renting out the minutes and traveling from village to village to sell the service.

Kiva is also amazing.
